Just thought I'd drop by.
Um...

13:57.546 --> 13:58.838
I'm sorry

13:58.922 --> 14:00.715
for, uh, taking off
like I did yesterday.

14:02.092 --> 14:04.344
No, I don't blame you.
I was a wreck.

14:04.427 --> 14:05.929
[Cam] Oh, it's fine.

14:06.012 --> 14:07.931
Um...

14:08.014 --> 14:09.975
do you want to maybe go
for a bike ride?

14:10.058 --> 14:12.310
I know this really cool spot.

14:12.394 --> 14:13.728
Sure. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

14:13.812 --> 14:15.230
Let me, um, let me go change.

14:15.313 --> 14:17.524
Okay. Cool.

14:17.607 --> 14:19.609
♪ ♪

14:23.196 --> 14:24.489
Oh... That's all breast meat

14:24.573 --> 14:26.116
with the special
pesto aioli sauce, right?

14:26.199 --> 14:28.493
I'm not your personal chef,
all right? But yes.

14:28.577 --> 14:30.287
I walked all the way
to the kitchen to get it.

14:30.370 --> 14:31.705
Mmm. Mmm.

14:31.788 --> 14:33.290
- You know it's all love.
- [Steven] Mm-hmm.

14:33.373 --> 14:34.457
Enjoy this, man.

14:34.540 --> 14:35.709
- [Jeremiah chuckles]
- [Gigi] Steven.

14:35.792 --> 14:37.752
Can we please get two Slushies?

14:37.836 --> 14:39.296
Mm. Yeah, yeah,
coming up, ladies.

14:39.379 --> 14:41.548
Thank you. Um, that was
the most fun waltz rehearsal,

14:41.631 --> 14:43.717
- like, in the history
of waltz rehearsals.
- Yeah.

14:43.800 --> 14:46.386
You came just in time. Your girl
Belly's a disaster in heels.

14:46.469 --> 14:48.138
You know what?
Belly's actually a good dancer.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.098
The waltz is just dumb.

14:54.394 --> 14:56.521
- Here you go, ladies.
- [Gigi] Perfect,

14:56.605 --> 14:57.981
- thank you.
- Always.

14:58.064 --> 14:59.691
There you go.

15:00.984 --> 15:02.068
- [Dara] What was that about?
- What's their deal?

15:02.152 --> 15:04.404
Well, uh, Gigi wants a boyfriend

15:04.487 --> 15:05.697
and, uh, Dara bit me once.

15:05.780 --> 15:08.617
- [Steven laughs]
- Yeah, it's a long story.

15:08.700 --> 15:10.452
- You want to get out of here?
- I can't.

15:10.535 --> 15:11.995
You're no fun.

15:12.078 --> 15:13.872
Not-not all of us have
a trust fund, Jere, all right?

15:13.955 --> 15:15.332
Some of us need to work.

15:15.415 --> 15:17.667
Bullshit. If Shayla
called you right now,

15:17.751 --> 15:19.336
- your ass would be
out the door.
- Yeah.

15:19.419 --> 15:21.379
- [laughs] I mean, it's Shayla.
- [Alex] Steven.

15:21.463 --> 15:22.839
Someone important must like you,

15:22.922 --> 15:24.549
because you've been promoted
to the card room.

15:24.633 --> 15:26.968
- Whoa.
- The club has a card room?

15:27.052 --> 15:29.512
- Come on.
- Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah.

15:33.975 --> 15:35.518
Mmm.

15:40.815 --> 15:43.026
♪ ♪

15:45.236 --> 15:47.238
[squawking]

15:48.406 --> 15:50.950
[Belly] I can't believe
I've never been here before.

15:51.034 --> 15:52.202
[Cam] Yeah.

15:52.285 --> 15:53.703
I've been coming here
since I was a kid.

15:53.787 --> 15:55.705
My mom used to bring me,
and, um...

15:55.789 --> 15:58.290
it's actually where
I spotted my first whale.

15:58.375 --> 16:00.251
Wow.

16:03.296 --> 16:05.632
Um... brought us

16:05.715 --> 16:07.717
some avocado
and sprout sandwiches.

16:07.801 --> 16:09.260
Thank you.

16:13.306 --> 16:15.141
[Cam] I made them.

16:16.142 --> 16:17.352
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

16:17.435 --> 16:19.562
[both laughing]

16:19.646 --> 16:21.439
[Belly] He's so nice.

16:21.523 --> 16:23.733
I could hang out with him
like this all summer

16:23.817 --> 16:26.111
and be really happy.

16:26.194 --> 16:29.739
But I can't help thinking that
I wish I was here with Conrad.

16:32.492 --> 16:34.661
[whistle blowing]

16:34.744 --> 16:37.205
Hey, Billy!
Stop running. All right?

16:37.288 --> 16:39.040
It's bad enough we had to shut
down the pool because of you.

16:39.124 --> 16:40.917
[Billy] It wasn't me,
jerk face.

16:41.000 --> 16:43.712
Watching Jeremiah fight
with his child nemesis

16:43.795 --> 16:45.964
literally never gets old.

16:46.047 --> 16:49.008
God! That kid is demonic,
I swear.

16:49.092 --> 16:50.385
Where's your brother been
all day?

16:50.468 --> 16:52.011
He's not texting me back.

16:52.095 --> 16:54.723
Conrad is too much drama,
Nicole.

16:54.806 --> 16:56.725
Oh, my God.

16:56.808 --> 17:00.145
- Frank Ocean is playing
the Yarmouth Music Festival.
- [gasps]

17:00.228 --> 17:01.521
[Nicole] Stop.
My dad's firm reps him.

17:01.604 --> 17:02.814
I can totally get us tickets.

17:02.897 --> 17:04.190
- For real?
- Yes.

17:04.273 --> 17:05.400
- [Shayla] Oh, my God.
- Well, you know, actually,

17:05.483 --> 17:08.153
uh, Conrad's been wanting
to go to Yarmouth.

17:08.236 --> 17:10.655
- Does he like Frank Ocean?
- Loves him.

17:10.739 --> 17:11.906
Yeah, yeah.
He's just been dealing

17:11.990 --> 17:12.949
with a lot of stuff
with our dad,

17:13.031 --> 17:14.367
- you know.
- Oh.

17:14.451 --> 17:15.617
But you should take him.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.537
- Yes.
- And I could bring Steven.

17:17.619 --> 17:19.955
- Yes. [inhales]
- Let's be cheesy

17:20.039 --> 17:22.000
- and rent a limo.
- Let's. I'll text my dad.

17:22.083 --> 17:23.167
[girls yelp, giggle]

17:23.251 --> 17:25.377
Jere, you're an amazing brother.

17:25.462 --> 17:26.838
[Nicole] Yeah.

17:26.921 --> 17:28.590
[indistinct chatter]

17:28.673 --> 17:30.550
♪ ♪

17:30.633 --> 17:32.677
[Cleveland] Whoa,
he's a big one.

17:32.761 --> 17:34.345
That's definitely a keeper.

17:34.429 --> 17:35.472
Uh-huh. In here.

17:35.555 --> 17:36.848
Whew.

17:38.224 --> 17:40.226
[Conrad exhales]

17:40.310 --> 17:42.270
[Cleveland] Whew.

17:42.353 --> 17:44.355
- All right.
- You ready to head back?

17:44.439 --> 17:47.108
Eh... not until you tell me
about your mystery girl.

17:47.192 --> 17:48.401
Uh...

17:48.485 --> 17:50.361
There it is again. Huh?

17:50.445 --> 17:52.906
Uh, it's just...
You know, I mean...

17:52.989 --> 17:55.200
We grew up together,
so I've always thought of her

17:55.283 --> 17:56.618
as this little kid.

17:56.701 --> 17:58.286
But now...

17:58.369 --> 18:00.622
she's...

18:00.705 --> 18:02.332
not.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.501
- And you like her.
- No.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.503
- Well, I don't know.
I mean, uh...
- [chuckles]

18:08.963 --> 18:11.800
I just have... there's just
so much shit going on.

18:11.883 --> 18:13.676
If we started something,

18:13.760 --> 18:16.471
I feel like I could...
fuck it up.

18:19.766 --> 18:21.768
Well...

18:21.851 --> 18:23.978
if there's one thing
I learned from

18:24.062 --> 18:26.397
years of overpriced therapy,

18:26.481 --> 18:28.024
it's that you can't be good
with someone else

18:28.107 --> 18:30.318
until you're good with yourself.

18:30.401 --> 18:33.112
That's how I tanked
my last relationship.

18:38.034 --> 18:40.453
[Belly] Is that a whale?

18:40.537 --> 18:42.413
Um...

18:42.497 --> 18:44.290
Oh! Nice spot.

18:44.374 --> 18:47.085
That is a young,
female humpback.

18:50.421 --> 18:52.382
- You see it?
- [Belly] Mm.

18:52.465 --> 18:54.384
Whew!

18:54.467 --> 18:56.636
She's a beauty.
You know what?

18:56.719 --> 18:58.847
Think this calls
for some dessert.

18:58.930 --> 19:01.182
Fruit Roll-Ups.

19:04.561 --> 19:06.354
Cam, I-I can't.

19:07.772 --> 19:09.315
I-I thought you said
these were your favorite.

19:09.399 --> 19:11.568
No, they're... I-I love them.
They're awesome.

19:11.651 --> 19:13.570
And-and you're awesome.

19:14.904 --> 19:17.407
Um...

19:17.490 --> 19:19.075
But, um...

19:19.158 --> 19:21.160
But...

19:21.244 --> 19:23.162
Yeah.

19:26.833 --> 19:29.252
Kind of saw this coming.
[chuckles]

19:29.335 --> 19:32.130
When you, um, didn't ask me
to be your escort.

19:32.213 --> 19:33.631
I'm sorry.
I was, I was planning to...

19:33.715 --> 19:35.508
It's okay. You don't have to...

19:35.592 --> 19:37.760
do the whole speech, that's all.

19:39.345 --> 19:44.726
The why or the who
doesn't really matter.

19:44.767 --> 19:47.312
- [♪ Bruno Major:
"Places We Won't Walk"]
- ♪ Family look on...

19:47.395 --> 19:49.898
I obviously know the who.

19:49.939 --> 19:53.234
♪ Decorate the floor...

19:53.318 --> 19:55.653
I didn't mean to hurt you.

19:55.737 --> 19:56.863
I know.

19:56.946 --> 19:58.364
Um...

19:58.448 --> 20:01.075
♪ In places we won't walk ♪

20:01.159 --> 20:02.744
I'm bummed.

20:02.827 --> 20:04.579
But, um...

20:04.662 --> 20:06.789
I'll be fine.

20:08.833 --> 20:12.503
♪ Children cry
and laugh and play ♪

20:12.587 --> 20:17.425
♪ Slowly hair
will turn to gray...

20:17.508 --> 20:20.720
Carpe diem, Flavia.

20:25.141 --> 20:28.811
You should be with the person
you really want to be with.

20:31.439 --> 20:33.650
And I hope he treats you right.

20:38.446 --> 20:41.491
- [♪ Jack Harlow: "Nail Tech"]
- ♪ Mm-mm, mm, mm-mm ♪

20:41.574 --> 20:45.244
♪ My nail tech knows
how to keep a little secret ♪

20:45.328 --> 20:47.956
♪ I don't wish for my success,
I speak it ♪

20:48.039 --> 20:49.624
♪ Walk around
with my chest out ♪

20:49.707 --> 20:51.209
♪ And my skin smooth,
I'm healthy...

20:51.292 --> 20:53.753
[groans]

20:53.836 --> 20:55.546
- ♪ Most of y'all
ain't wealthy ♪
- ♪ No ♪

20:55.630 --> 20:57.966
♪ Most of y'all just dress
like it, I caught the vibe...

20:58.049 --> 21:01.386
Steve-O! You get
my extra jalapeños?

21:01.469 --> 21:02.762
Yes, sir. I told the chef

21:02.845 --> 21:04.639
- to drown it in green.
- [chuckles] Good man.

21:04.722 --> 21:07.517
You know, you look like
a smart kid. You know poker?

21:07.600 --> 21:08.768
Well, I've dabbled.

21:08.851 --> 21:10.853
You got a theory
on pocket twos?

21:10.937 --> 21:13.314
Well, I generally play them.

21:17.527 --> 21:21.197
- [man 2] All in.
- Big mistake. I'll call.

21:21.280 --> 21:22.490
You better be right, kid.

21:22.573 --> 21:24.701
Uh, well, I didn't mean
for you to bet it all.

21:26.160 --> 21:27.412
[man 2 groans]

21:28.454 --> 21:31.082
- [man 3] Ooh.
- [man 2 laughing]

21:35.211 --> 21:37.714
Oh, that better be a two,
or I just lost a Tesla payment.

21:37.797 --> 21:40.258
- [chuckles]
- [man 2] Come on. Come to Papa.

21:40.341 --> 21:42.719
Come on, baby.

21:42.802 --> 21:44.303
- Yes!
- [laughter]

21:44.387 --> 21:47.015
- Ah.
- Boom! I told you,

21:47.098 --> 21:49.475
I like this kid. Ah.

21:49.559 --> 21:50.893
[Steven chuckles]

21:50.977 --> 21:53.438
Yeah, that's beautiful.
Thank you. Here you go.

21:53.521 --> 21:55.356
Thanks for the assist.

21:55.440 --> 21:57.608
Uh, thank you.

21:57.692 --> 21:59.861
[man 2] Appreciate it.

21:59.902 --> 22:02.947
Well, that was exciting.

22:03.031 --> 22:04.490
- [♪ Tai Verdes: "Feeling This
Bad Never Felt So Great"]
- ♪ I miss the spark ♪

22:04.574 --> 22:06.075
♪ I miss you showin' me
all of your art ♪

22:06.159 --> 22:08.244
♪ Either we go together
or we fall apart ♪

22:08.327 --> 22:10.705
♪ Every day is hard ♪

22:10.788 --> 22:12.707
♪ I'm learnin'
to be with just me ♪

22:12.790 --> 22:14.709
♪ Up in my head,
it gets scary ♪

22:14.792 --> 22:16.461
♪ Haven't called you back
in weeks ♪

22:16.544 --> 22:18.171
♪ But this is the first time
I'm carefree ♪

22:18.254 --> 22:22.091
♪ Feeling this bad
never felt so great ♪

22:22.175 --> 22:26.095
♪ Never thought
I'd be happy today ♪

22:26.179 --> 22:30.183
♪ Now that you're gone
and out of my way ♪

22:30.266 --> 22:34.771
♪ Feeling this bad
never felt so great ♪

22:34.854 --> 22:38.274
♪ Ooh-ooh, ooh, ooh-ooh ♪

22:38.357 --> 22:41.110
♪ Feeling this bad
never felt so great...

22:41.194 --> 22:43.321
Hey. What's with the crown?

22:43.404 --> 22:46.115
My mom's out to paint me as
Hermes, messenger of the gods.

22:46.199 --> 22:48.451
Cool.

22:48.534 --> 22:50.453
Who you looking for?

22:50.536 --> 22:54.082
Um, I thought maybe
Conrad would be back by now.

22:56.375 --> 22:57.335
[sighs]

22:57.418 --> 22:59.003
Where have you been?

22:59.087 --> 23:01.089
I, uh, had a picnic with Cam.

23:01.172 --> 23:03.466
Oh, cute. How is Cam Cameron?

23:03.549 --> 23:06.844
I don't think
we're gonna hang out anymore.

23:06.928 --> 23:08.304
Oh.

23:09.889 --> 23:13.684
Well, poor Cam Cameron.

23:13.768 --> 23:15.812
[laughs] You guys were never
gonna let that go.

23:15.895 --> 23:17.939
[laughing]
No.

23:18.022 --> 23:21.109
For the record, I liked him.

23:22.360 --> 23:23.861
And you don't look that upset.

23:23.945 --> 23:25.488
But, if you are,

23:25.571 --> 23:27.573
this little nugget
will cheer you up.

23:27.657 --> 23:30.284
Our moms--
high-key stoned right now.

23:30.368 --> 23:32.537
- No way!
- Yeah.

23:32.620 --> 23:33.871
All my favorite snacks are gone.

23:33.955 --> 23:36.415
Courtney did not kill Kurt.

23:36.499 --> 23:38.251
Oh, come on.
Did you see that documentary?

23:38.334 --> 23:40.044
Everybody knew
he wanted to divorce her,

23:40.128 --> 23:44.048
and with him dead, she got
all his music, everything.

23:44.132 --> 23:46.884
You know, Dave Grohl says he
still can't listen to Nirvana,

23:46.968 --> 23:48.803
it's too painful.

23:48.886 --> 23:50.304
I still don't feel anything.

23:50.388 --> 23:52.306
[Susannah] I'm hungry.
We should make lasagna!

23:52.390 --> 23:53.808
[gasps] I love lasagna.

23:53.891 --> 23:57.603
Shoot! I need
to go shopping. Mm.

23:57.645 --> 23:59.897
Mm.

23:59.981 --> 24:02.525
- Look.
- What's that?

24:02.608 --> 24:05.444
- Yum.
- Oh.

24:05.528 --> 24:08.114
Good. Mm-hmm, yummy.

24:08.197 --> 24:09.532
- Not bad at all.
- [Susannah laughs]

24:09.615 --> 24:11.826
- Holy cow.
- I told you.

24:11.909 --> 24:13.870
- Oh. Hey.
- [laughs] Oh!

24:13.953 --> 24:17.874
- Our beautiful babies!
- Oh, look at them! Mmm.

24:17.957 --> 24:20.918
Ooh, they're so cute!
Mm, you, come with me.

24:21.002 --> 24:22.920
I got to get you
while the light's still good.

24:23.004 --> 24:25.381
Okay, well, let's do that.

24:25.464 --> 24:27.466
[Susannah laughs]

24:27.550 --> 24:29.260
♪ Like the setting sun...

24:29.343 --> 24:31.387
Oh, what have you guys
been doing?

24:31.470 --> 24:34.473
Oh, just talking, snacking.

24:34.557 --> 24:38.936
Hey, what do you think
of this text?

24:40.730 --> 24:42.398
Oh, my God.
The guy you hooked up with

24:42.481 --> 24:43.983
last night was
Cleveland Castillo?

24:44.066 --> 24:45.359
It wasn't planned.
One thing led to another,

24:45.443 --> 24:46.736
and we ended up
having sex in my car.

24:46.819 --> 24:47.987
♪ La-la-la-la-la ♪♪

24:48.070 --> 24:49.363
I am not listening.

24:49.447 --> 24:51.949
What did I say?

24:54.285 --> 24:57.246
[Susannah] Oh. Oh.

24:57.330 --> 24:59.624
My boy. Look at you!

24:59.707 --> 25:02.210
Oh, this light is beautiful.
Can you feel it?

25:02.293 --> 25:05.296
Can you feel the softness?

25:05.379 --> 25:06.839
I can feel it.

25:06.923 --> 25:08.466
- [laughs]
- Oh, my God.

25:08.549 --> 25:10.468
I just want to dance with you.

25:10.551 --> 25:12.511
[Jeremiah laughs]

25:12.595 --> 25:14.680
Dance with me? [laughs]

25:15.723 --> 25:17.683
[inhales]
Oh, my little boy.

25:17.767 --> 25:21.062
[laughs]

25:21.145 --> 25:23.773
Have a seat.

25:23.856 --> 25:26.817
Ah, how is your summer,
my love? You happy?

25:26.901 --> 25:28.945
- Yeah, yeah.
- [laughs]

25:29.028 --> 25:31.364
It feels a little bit different
this summer, though.

25:31.447 --> 25:35.326
Mm. Summer's the same.

25:35.409 --> 25:37.828
We're the ones who are changing.

25:37.912 --> 25:39.538
Well, except you.

25:39.622 --> 25:41.290
I don't want you
to ever change. [laughs]

25:41.374 --> 25:43.251
[Belly] Jeremiah,
please save me!

25:43.334 --> 25:45.711
My mom wants to braid my hair!

25:45.795 --> 25:47.797
- Oh, God.
- [laughs]

25:47.880 --> 25:50.091
Oh, you're such
a good friend to Belly.

25:50.174 --> 25:52.718
Like a brother. [laughs]

25:54.845 --> 25:57.848
All right, enough
with the commentary, Mom.

25:57.932 --> 26:00.101
Let's see the art.

26:00.184 --> 26:02.728
[Susannah] What do you think?

26:02.812 --> 26:05.564
I think
it might be my best work.

26:05.648 --> 26:07.650
Belly?!

26:16.951 --> 26:19.996
Ah, it's, um...

26:20.079 --> 26:21.580
[Jeremiah] Mm-hmm.

26:21.664 --> 26:25.751
Picasso and Jackson Pollock
had a baby.

26:25.835 --> 26:27.378
What?

26:31.507 --> 26:34.468
[laughing] Oh, my God,
it's terrible!

26:34.552 --> 26:35.636
[laughter]

26:35.720 --> 26:38.681
[Susannah] It's so bad!

26:38.764 --> 26:41.726
See, this is why
old people should not do drugs.

26:41.809 --> 26:44.270
- How dare you! Outraged!
- Such...

26:44.353 --> 26:46.856
- [laughter]
- Such blatant ageism.

26:46.939 --> 26:49.900
Let's leave these brats

26:49.984 --> 26:52.820
and go walk on the beach.

26:52.903 --> 26:54.947
I need my sweater.

26:55.031 --> 26:56.532
- Have fun, Mom!
- Bye.

26:56.615 --> 26:58.951
- Bye, brats.
- Bye.

26:59.035 --> 27:00.745
Wow.

27:00.828 --> 27:03.414
Louis XIII, a lousy French king,

27:03.497 --> 27:05.416
- one hell of a cognac.
- [whistling]

27:05.499 --> 27:08.127
Buddy, you are a lifesaver.
[clears throat]

27:09.712 --> 27:12.256
Uh-oh. Are you old enough
to serve booze?

27:12.340 --> 27:13.674
[Steven] Oh, please.

27:13.758 --> 27:15.760
I thought this was
a private club.

27:15.843 --> 27:17.511
[laughter]

27:17.595 --> 27:20.014
[exhaling rhythmically]

27:20.097 --> 27:23.225
[phone buzzing]

27:23.309 --> 27:25.102
Hello? Are we playing cards,
or what?

27:25.186 --> 27:26.771
Sorry, my wife's blowing me up.

27:26.854 --> 27:28.773
My daughter's SAT tutor
is late again.

27:28.856 --> 27:31.817
Oh, man, my SAT tutor
was a monster.

27:31.901 --> 27:33.652
I'm so glad those days
are over.

27:33.736 --> 27:35.613
Yeah, well, I'm sure you got
a perfect score.

27:35.696 --> 27:37.198
[laughter]

27:37.281 --> 27:39.617
One of the partners
